1.	https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/deployment/jar/build.html

2.	create JAR File: jar cf jar-file input-file(s)
input-files argument can contain the wildcard * symbol. If contents of those directories, the contents of the directories are added to the JAR achieve recursively.

3.	Default Manifest (must be UTF8):
Manifest-Version:1.0
Created-By: 1.7.0_06
Main-Class: classname (optional)

4.	Manifest default path: META-INF/MANIFEST.MF

5.	Modifying a Manifest File: jar cfm jar-file manifest-addition input-files
The manifest must end with a new line or carriage return.
manifest-addition contains entries: HeaderName:Value

6.	Run the program in jar: java –jar jar-file

7.	Adding Classes to the JAR Files’ Classpath.
Class-Path:jar1-name jar2-name directory-name/jar3-name
jar1-name should on the local network. 
